Per the Comprehensive Rules, protection is a static ability that permanents have (CR 702.15a). Static abilities are active only while a permanent is on the battlefield (CR 112.3d) and a card ceases to be a permanent if it is not on the battlefield (CR 110.1).

So no. Akroma's protection works only while she's a permanent (i.e. on the battlefield). She is not a permanent if she is in the graveyard, hand, or library; thus, she isn't protected in those zones.

However, [autocard]Necromancy[/autocard] and [autocard]Animate Dead[/autocard] bring a creature back onto the battlefield and attach themselves to that creature. When Akroma is brought onto the battlefield, she has protection from black. Akroma's ability will cause these enchantments to be unable to attach themselves to her, and she will be sacrificed. [autocard]Zombify[/autocard], [autocard]Buried Alive[/autocard], [autocard]Reanimate[/autocard] or [autocard]Surgical Extraction[/autocard] will work on her, because they don't target or attach to her while she is on the battlefield.

